[2026-06-21T11:20:14.127Z +7.6s] stderr> # Regen meta-prompt — Take 2 (depth & dimensionality)
[2026-06-21T11:20:14.128Z +7.6s] stderr> 3. **Matching the start and end frames** — the shot must begin exactly as frame 1 and settle exactly into frame 2.
[2026-06-21T11:20:14.128Z +7.6s] stderr> 2. **Consistency** — preserve identity, scale, geometry, materials, exposure, and lighting across every frame.
[2026-06-21T11:20:14.128Z +7.6s] stderr> Look at both frames closely. Identify the subjects, their orientation, setting, lighting, materials, and any visible text or logos. Note exactly what changes between the two frames.
[2026-06-21T11:20:14.128Z +7.6s] stderr> ## Rules
[2026-06-21T11:20:14.128Z +7.6s] stderr> Write one concise paragraph (3–4 sentences): name the look; describe the start; describe one uninterrupted, physically motivated camera move or real-world action; then describe the end.
[2026-06-21T11:20:14.128Z +7.6s] stderr> Use a single smooth motion path with gentle acceleration and deceleration: establish the start pose briefly, move at a steady believable pace, and settle into the end pose without a sudden final snap. Every subject, prop, and the camera must follow continuous screen-space trajectories with consistent momentum, weight, contact, and occlusion; preserve identity, scale, geometry, materials, exposure, and lighting from frame to frame. Prioritize camera movement, natural object motion, or a visible causal action. Use a transformation only when the frames clearly support a physically plausible mechanism. The shot must be continuous and stable, with no fade, dissolve, cut, teleportation, time skip, speed ramp, freeze, jitter, flicker, melting, warping, duplication, or spontaneous object replacement.
[2026-06-21T11:20:14.128Z +7.6s] stderr> Audio: describe only natural, continuous ambient/diegetic sound that fits the scene — no music, speech, or abrupt changes — so it blends seamlessly when the clip is spliced in.
[2026-06-21T11:20:14.128Z +7.6s] stderr> 4. **Take direction (lowest priority)** — the creative lean in the section below. Apply it only when it does **not** compromise 1–3. If it conflicts at all, drop it.
[2026-06-21T11:20:14.128Z +7.6s] stderr> Fold the key avoidances into the positive paragraph too, so it stands alone when the provider takes no negative_prompt.
[2026-06-21T11:20:14.128Z +7.6s] stderr> If text/logos appear, state that they stay crisp and legible. If the endpoints cannot plausibly connect in one shot, say so in the note rather than inventing a magical bridge.
[2026-06-21T11:20:14.128Z +7.6s] stderr> Write a `negative_prompt` as a comma-separated list covering: fade, dissolve, cut, teleportation, time skip, speed ramp, freeze, jitter, flicker, melting, warping, morphing glitches, distorted or smeared text/logos, deformed subjects, duplicate or extra objects, unwanted hands/people, fast erratic motion, wobble, low quality, blur, artifacts, watermark — plus any frame-specific failure you can anticipate.
[2026-06-21T11:20:14.128Z +7.6s] stderr> ## Take 2 direction (lowest priority — never override the rules above)
[2026-06-21T11:20:14.128Z +7.6s] stderr> ## Output format — exactly this, nothing else
[2026-06-21T11:20:14.128Z +7.6s] stderr> Lean toward **depth and dimensionality**: favor a move that reveals parallax and layered space — foreground, midground, and background separating naturally — and read the existing light as soft volumetric depth so the scene feels three-dimensional and inviting to look into. Use only the depth that is already implied by the two frames; invent no new objects, light sources, or geometry. This is purely to make the clip a little more visually engaging; abandon it the instant it threatens realism, consistency, or the exact match to the start/end frames.
[2026-06-21T11:20:14.128Z +7.6s] stderr> ```
[2026-06-21T11:20:14.128Z +7.6s] stderr> negative_prompt: <comma-separated list>
[2026-06-21T11:20:14.128Z +7.6s] stderr> note: <one-line feasibility warning, only if relevant>
[2026-06-21T11:20:14.128Z +7.6s] stderr> prompt: <one paragraph>
[2026-06-21T11:20:14.128Z +7.6s] stderr> ```
